			<div class="wills_header_text_box">
				<h1 class="main_header">When Is A Specific Power Of Attorney Needed?</h1>
				<h5 class="heading_description">A power of attorney must state specifically that someone has the authority to:</h5>
				<ol class="witness_qualifications">
					<li><h5>Sell, buy or lease anything.</h5></li>
					<li class="internal_list_item"><h5>Give a gift.</h5></li>
					<li class="internal_list_item"><h5>Accept or reject a succession (inheritance.)</h5></li>
					<li class="internal_list_item"><h5>Take out a loan, settle a debt, or become a surety.</h5></li>
					<li class="internal_list_item"><h5>Write or sign checks and promissory notes.</h5></li>
					<li class="internal_list_item"><h5>Enter into a compromise or take something to arbitration.</h5></li>
					<li class="internal_list_item"><h5>Make any healthcare decisions, such as surgery or medication decisions.</h5></li>
					<li class="internal_list_item"><h5>Stop or limit communications between the principal and a relative or close friend.</h5></li>
				</ol>
			</div>

